properties.areaDesc: Juneau Borough and Northern Admiralty Island
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 19 at 2:15PM AKST until February 20 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Juneau.

* WHEN...From Thursday afternoon through Thursday evening.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Unsecured boats
could break loose. High winds could affect the evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The best chances for high wind gusts look
to occur in the late afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH THURSDAY EVENING
